snippet.textDisplay:
Just by doing some research, his swimming was within allowed rules. The head needs to be above water at all times. So no front crawl is allowed like some commentators mentioned. I believe that the water-polo crawl style where the head is above water could be allowed but its pretty hard for someone who doesn't train it.
You cant lose form with push ups, if you do, you're out.
Sit ups need to be done with elbows touching the knees or a couple inches lower than that. He went above that every time so pretty good.
And pull ups, you cant let go of the bar at any point or you're out.
Running is self explanatory, just beat the minimum time :) not on a treadmill tho, because not the same muscles are engaged as running around in the heat and a hard surface.
Feel free to correct me if I said something wrong. I'm still damn impressed with how well he did as it is.
